'''BioDiscovery Toronto''' (BDT) is an organization of nine [[non-profit]] [[biomedical]] research institutions in [[Toronto]].<ref>{{cite web|work =Market Wired |title =BioDiscovery Toronto Welcomes Toronto Rehabilitation Institute |url =http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/biodiscovery-toronto-welcomes-toronto-rehabilitation-institute-572394.htm}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work =MarsDD |title =Toronto's $25 million commercialization "engine" celebrates the appointment of its Board of Directors |url =https://www.marsdd.com/media-centre/marsinnovation-02062009}}</ref>
The organization acts as a [[wikt:Special:Search/clearing house|clearing house]] for private companies seeking biomedical expertise. It gives access to research and biomedical facilities.
The member institutions are: * the [[Centre for Addiction and Mental Health]] * [[Mount Sinai Hospital (Toronto)|Mount Sinai Hospital]] * [[Ryerson University]] * [[St. Michael's Hospital (Toronto)|St. Michael's Hospital]] * [[Sunnybrook Health Sciences Centre]] * The [[Hospital for Sick Children]] * [[Toronto Rehabilitation Institute]] * the [[University Health Network]] * the [[University of Toronto]]
