{{Other uses|Tabaré (disambiguation){{!}}Tabaré}}
'''''Tabaré''''' is an [[epic poem]] written by [[Uruguay]]an poet [[Juan Zorrilla de San Martín]].<ref>[http://portal.artelatino.com/foros/juan-zorrilla-por-francisco-arias-solis Juan Zorrilla por Francisco Arias Solís.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303182559/http://portal.artelatino.com/foros/juan-zorrilla-por-francisco-arias-solis |date=2016-03-03 }} {{es icon}}</ref> 

Written in 1886, it was published for the first time in 1888. The poem comprises 4736 [[Verse (poetry)|verse]]s divided into 10 [[canto]]s. The love story between the aboriginal Tabaré and the Spaniard Blanca is a metaphor of the fate of the [[Charrúa]] people who originally inhabited the [[Banda Oriental]].<ref>[http://www.autoresdeluruguay.uy/biblioteca/raul_montero_bustamante/archivo/textos/Prologo_Tabare.pdf Prólogo a ''Tabaré'' por Raúl Montero Bustamante] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303191241/http://www.autoresdeluruguay.uy/biblioteca/raul_montero_bustamante/archivo/textos/Prologo_Tabare.pdf |date=2016-03-03 }} {{es icon}}</ref>
